# Finance Management System

A simple console-based finance management application for tracking transactions and calculating balances.

# Requirements

- Windows OS

- .NET Framework 4.7.2 (comes pre-installed on most Windows versions)

- Command Prompt or PowerShell

# Project Structure

- FinanceManagementSystem/
  ├── Accounts/
  ├── Interfaces/
  ├── Models/
  ├── Processors/
  ├── FinanceApp.cs
  ├── Program.cs
  ├── FinanceManagementSystem.csproj
  └── bin/
  └── Debug/
  └── FinanceManagementSystem.exe \*

# How to Run the Project

### 1. Clone or download this repository.

### 2. Open Command Prompt and navigate to the main project folder:

\*cd "C:\Users\<YourName>\Desktop\dcit318-assignment3-11116390\FinanceManagementSystem"

-

### 3. Build the project (if not already built):

msbuild FinanceManagementSystem.csproj

### 4. Navigate to the compiled output folder:

_cd bin\Debug_

### 5. Run the application:

_FinanceManagementSystem.exe _

## Features

- Add transactions with ID, amount, and description.

- View all transactions.

- Calculate the current balance.

- Simple text-based menu system.

# Notes

- This project is built using .NET Framework 4.7.2 (not .NET Core).

- If you want to run using dotnet run, you need to upgrade to .NET 6/7 and convert to SDK-style project.
